Oh, Christ, yes. You've seen
her with her clothes off.

735
01:00:35,981 --> 01:00:39,179
Faces are a doddle
compared to tits and ass.

736
01:00:39,284 --> 01:00:42,253
-No hairline.
-Oh, really, Louis!

737
01:00:43,722 --> 01:00:46,190
I've been looking for
you everywhere, Ida.

738
01:00:50,730 --> 01:00:53,630
Mother. Mother, I have to talk to Mr.
Helpmann.

739
01:00:53,733 --> 01:00:57,362
-Oh, you stupid sod.
-Dear boy.

740
01:00:57,469 --> 01:00:59,733
What do you think
of your mother now?

741
01:00:59,838 --> 01:01:01,806
<i>It'll never last.</i>

742
01:01:04,143 --> 01:01:06,043
Excuse me.

743
01:01:06,144 --> 01:01:08,670
Dr. Chapman, did
you say something?

744
01:01:08,780 --> 01:01:10,748
That technique... I've tried it.

745
01:01:10,849 --> 01:01:14,251
Oh, nice effect, but
highly unstable.

746
01:01:14,353 --> 01:01:18,550
<i>In six months she'll
look like Grandma Moses.</i>

747
01:01:18,657 --> 01:01:23,561
Now, see here, Chapman, at least mine don't
end up looking like they've been mugged.

748
01:01:23,663 --> 01:01:26,257
Sam! Sam!

749
01:01:28,367 --> 01:01:33,235
<i>What have you done
with his body?</i>

750
01:01:33,338 --> 01:01:36,034
Sam!

751
01:01:36,141 --> 01:01:37,541
<i>Sam?</i>

752
01:01:37,643 --> 01:01:41,545
-What on earth's happened to you?
-There was a little complication.

753
01:01:41,646 --> 01:01:46,846
Dr. Chapman says it often happens
with a delicate skin like mine.

754
01:01:46,952 --> 01:01:48,853
Nothing to worry about.

755
01:01:48,954 --> 01:01:52,413
He's promised me these bandages
will be off in a jiffy.

756
01:01:52,525 --> 01:01:55,358
-Actually, there's someone I want to meet.
-Oh, I know.

757
01:01:55,460 --> 01:01:57,759
I know.

758
01:02:00,065 --> 01:02:02,534
There we are.

759
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:06,365
I'm going to leave you
two lovebirds in peace.

760
01:02:07,840 --> 01:02:09,739
Hello, Shirley.

761
01:02:09,842 --> 01:02:13,333
-Oh, God.
-Come on!

762
01:02:13,445 --> 01:02:15,414
Do you want a drink?

763
01:02:18,150 --> 01:02:20,481
Oh. Hello.

764
01:02:20,585 --> 01:02:23,487
Chase those years away!

765
01:02:23,588 --> 01:02:25,954
Listen, Shirley...

766
01:02:26,057 --> 01:02:30,119
your mother and my mother, they
seem to have got the idea that...

767
01:02:30,228 --> 01:02:32,628
Look, I'm very flattered
and, uh, well...

768
01:02:32,731 --> 01:02:35,632
I just don't want you to be
under any false impressions.

769
01:02:35,735 --> 01:02:37,635
It's all right.

770
01:02:37,737 --> 01:02:40,034
I don't like you either.

771
01:02:41,606 --> 01:02:43,574
<i>Sam!</i>

772
01:02:44,409 --> 01:02:46,708
Jack. Excuse me, Shirley.

773
01:02:46,811 --> 01:02:50,509
I'm s... I'm sorry.

774
01:02:51,550 --> 01:02:54,916
-Sam! You remember Alison?
-Evening.

775
01:02:55,021 --> 01:02:57,717
Alison. Sam Lowry. Old friend.

776
01:02:57,822 --> 01:03:00,052
Alison, yes, of course.

777
01:03:00,159 --> 01:03:03,059
-You look different.
-Well, I'm two years older.

778
01:03:03,161 --> 01:03:05,289
-And she's been to Dr. Jaffe.
-Ah.

779
01:03:05,398 --> 01:03:08,423
She doesn't like me telling people,
but, in fact, she's really pleased.

780
01:03:08,534 --> 01:03:12,264
-I knew there was something different.
-Remember how they used to stick out?

781
01:03:12,371 --> 01:03:16,431
What? Oh, yes. Uh, well, rather.

782
01:03:16,541 --> 01:03:19,840
-Always used to wonder if they were real.
-What, my ears?

783
01:03:21,213 --> 01:03:23,112
Sorry?

784
01:03:23,215 --> 01:03:25,342
Dr. Jaffe pinned her ears back.

785
01:03:25,451 --> 01:03:27,351
Yes, that's what I...

786
01:03:27,452 --> 01:03:29,717
Always used to wonder
if she wore falsies.

787
01:03:29,822 --> 01:03:32,085
Ah! Mr. Helpmann.

788
01:03:32,190 --> 01:03:35,057
False ears... Mr. Helpmann!

789
01:03:35,226 --> 01:03:37,786
-Hello, Jack.
-You remember my wife, Alison?

790
01:03:37,896 --> 01:03:39,797
Yes, of course.
Barbara, isn't it?

791
01:03:39,898 --> 01:03:41,798
-How are you?
-Well, actuall...

792
01:03:41,900 --> 01:03:44,802
Barbara's very well, thank you, sir.
Very well indeed. How are you?

793
01:03:44,903 --> 01:03:46,804
-Fine, thanks.
-Good.

794
01:03:46,905 --> 01:03:50,432
Hello, Sam. Ida said you might be here.
Have you got a minute?

795
01:03:50,543 --> 01:03:53,443
-Would you excuse us?
-Oh, no, of course.

796
01:03:53,545 --> 01:03:56,173
Of course. Come on, Alison...
Barbara.

797
01:03:57,650 --> 01:03:59,617
Sam.

798
01:04:02,788 --> 01:04:04,755
I need your help.

799
01:04:26,711 --> 01:04:29,271
Thanks very much, Sam.

800
01:04:29,380 --> 01:04:32,009
Mr. Helpmann, I'm
glad to be of help.

801
01:04:32,117 --> 01:04:35,679
-If I can help you...
-Ah, well, actually...

802
01:04:35,788 --> 01:04:37,778
Oh.

803
01:04:40,358 --> 01:04:43,260
Your father and I
were very close.

804
01:04:43,362 --> 01:04:47,695
Of course, Jeremiah was senior to
me, but we were close friends.

805
01:04:47,800 --> 01:04:50,233
Especially after the bombing.

806
01:04:51,402 --> 01:04:55,168
And I keep his name alive
at the office every day.

807
01:04:56,208 --> 01:04:58,869
It's as though he's there
still speaking to me.

808
01:04:58,978 --> 01:05:02,378
"'Ere I am.

809
01:05:02,481 --> 01:05:05,074
J.H."

810
01:05:06,719 --> 01:05:08,846
The ghost in the machine.

811
01:05:11,222 --> 01:05:14,681
I know he would have
wanted me to help you.

812
01:05:16,728 --> 01:05:19,128
And I promised your mother...

813
01:05:19,231 --> 01:05:23,634
that I'd take you on to the
team at Information Retrieval.

814
01:05:23,735 --> 01:05:26,068
But I gather that, um...

815
01:05:26,172 --> 01:05:30,905
Well, actually, Mr. Helpmann, I've, uh...
I've changed my mind.

816
01:05:31,010 --> 01:05:34,309
I've decided I'd
accept the transfer...

817
01:05:34,413 --> 01:05:36,380
if I'm not too late.

818
01:05:37,416 --> 01:05:39,315
Too late?

819
01:05:39,418 --> 01:05:41,476
That's for me to say.

820
01:05:41,586 --> 01:05:44,054
Well... Well, then, I, uh...

821
01:05:46,925 --> 01:05:49,393
Welcome to Information
Retrieval.

822
01:06:22,961 --> 01:06:24,929
Uh, my name's Lowry.

823
01:06:26,097 --> 01:06:28,088
Sam Lowry.

824
01:06:28,199 --> 01:06:31,601
I've been told to report
to Mr. Warrenn.

825
01:06:31,704 --> 01:06:33,831
<i>Thirtieth floor, sir.</i>

826
01:06:33,938 --> 01:06:35,907
<i>You're expected.</i>

827
01:06:37,576 --> 01:06:41,478
Um, don't you want to search me?

828
01:06:41,579 --> 01:06:43,547
<i>No, sir.</i>

829
01:06:44,817 --> 01:06:47,445
<i>-Want to see my I.D.?
-No need, sir.</i>

830
01:06:49,655 --> 01:06:52,885
<i>-But I could be anybody.
-No, you couldn't, sir.</i>

831
01:06:52,992 --> 01:06:55,893
<i>This is Information Retrieval.</i>

832
01:06:55,994 --> 01:06:59,123
<i>The lift's arrived, sir.</i>

833
01:08:21,512 --> 01:08:25,005
I want that order rescinded!

834
01:08:46,404 --> 01:08:48,430
<i>Half as terrorists,
the rest as victims.</i>

835
01:08:48,539 --> 01:08:50,201
Yes. No.

836
01:08:50,309 --> 01:08:52,037
Definitely no!

837
01:08:52,144 --> 01:08:54,840
-My name's Lowry, Mr. Warrenn. Sam Lowry.
-Ah, Lowry!

838
01:08:54,947 --> 01:08:59,440
Yes. No. Cancel that. Okay.

839
01:08:59,551 --> 01:09:01,984
-Glad to have you aboard. Yes.
-These requisitions...

840
01:09:02,087 --> 01:09:05,113
-Sir, I'd like to point this out...
-No! Don't be ridiculous, Jenkins.

841
01:09:05,224 --> 01:09:07,715
-About these invoices...
-Yes. Yes. Yes.

842
01:09:07,826 --> 01:09:09,987
You'll like it up here.
Send that back.

843
01:09:10,095 --> 01:09:13,257
We've got a crack team of... Are
they kidding? ... decision makers.

844
01:09:13,364 --> 01:09:15,265
No, in triplicate.

845
01:09:15,367 --> 01:09:17,835
I'm expecting big things...
Two copies to Financial!

846
01:09:17,935 --> 01:09:21,837
No. No. Don't let
Progress see those.

847
01:09:21,939 --> 01:09:25,534
Between you and me, Lowry, this... No, no!
Department... Tell Records to get stuffed!

848
01:09:25,644 --> 01:09:27,543
Is about to be upgraded and...

849
01:09:27,645 --> 01:09:31,412
Ah! Here we are.

850
01:09:31,516 --> 01:09:34,747
<i>Your very own number
on your very own door.</i>

851
01:09:34,853 --> 01:09:37,753
And behind that door,
your very own office.

852
01:09:37,855 --> 01:09:40,756
Congratulations, DZ/015.

853
01:09:40,859 --> 01:09:42,884
Welcome to the team.

854
01:09:42,994 --> 01:09:45,360
Yes! No! Cancel that!

855
01:09:45,463 --> 01:09:47,728
<i>Send two copies to Financial!</i>

856
01:11:21,726 --> 01:11:23,627
Well, you can't borrow
any more chairs!

857
01:11:23,729 --> 01:11:26,288
There's only one left in here
now, and I need that to sit on!

858
01:11:26,398 --> 01:11:27,989
What?

859
01:11:28,100 --> 01:11:30,125
Oh.

860
01:11:30,234 --> 01:11:32,795
Sorry.

861
01:11:32,904 --> 01:11:34,963
Who are you?

862
01:11:35,073 --> 01:11:37,472
My name's Lowry. Sam Lowry.

863
01:11:37,576 --> 01:11:40,875
Oh, yes. The new boy
from next door.

864
01:11:41,913 --> 01:11:44,814
My name's Lime. Harvey Lime.

865
01:11:44,917 --> 01:11:46,817
Welcome to Expediting.

866
01:11:46,918 --> 01:11:49,819
I say, look, would you mind if I
borrowed your computer console?

867
01:11:49,921 --> 01:11:50,646
What?

868
01:11:50,671 --> 01:11:52,846
Yes, I'll let you have
it back in 10 minutes.

869
01:11:52,925 --> 01:11:56,520
You want to take my
console into your office?

870
01:11:56,627 --> 01:11:58,528
Yes. Just for a few minutes.

871
01:11:58,630 --> 01:12:00,654
I-I'll tell you what.

872
01:12:00,765 --> 01:12:02,756
You tell me what you want...

873
01:12:02,868 --> 01:12:05,029
and I'll do it for you.

874
01:12:05,136 --> 01:12:07,435
I'm a bit of a whiz
on that thing.

875
01:12:07,538 --> 01:12:09,439
Um...

876
01:12:09,541 --> 01:12:11,440
all right.

877
01:12:11,542 --> 01:12:15,377
Uh, I need some information
on a woman named Layton.

878
01:12:15,479 --> 01:12:17,448
A woman, eh?

879
01:12:17,548 --> 01:12:19,846
-I see.
-Yes.

880
01:12:19,952 --> 01:12:23,581
I know her age and distinguishing marks,
but I need an address or a place of work.

881
01:12:23,689 --> 01:12:26,590
This your dream girl, is it?

882
01:12:26,692 --> 01:12:28,853
What? Um...

883
01:12:28,961 --> 01:12:31,020
Look, let me use your console.

884
01:12:31,128 --> 01:12:33,029
You must be joking.

885
01:12:33,131 --> 01:12:38,125
When there's a woman involved,
there's no stopping me.

886
01:12:38,235 --> 01:12:40,203
Let's have that sheet.

887
01:12:49,180 --> 01:12:51,149
Sod it! It's broken!

888
01:12:51,248 --> 01:12:53,216
You haven't switched it on.

889
01:12:54,485 --> 01:12:56,453
Oh, yes.

890
01:13:00,024 --> 01:13:01,225
Look, you're putting
me off standing there.

891
01:13:01,226 --> 01:13:02,654
Why don't you go back to your office
and I'll give you a knock

892
01:13:02,679 --> 01:13:04,377
when I'm finished.
-Um...

893
01:13:06,163 --> 01:13:08,496
Go on. I'm not going
to elope with her.

894
01:13:10,002 --> 01:13:11,970
All right.

895
01:13:47,072 --> 01:13:49,801
Sam!

896
01:14:11,595 --> 01:14:14,189
Sam.

897
01:14:15,934 --> 01:14:17,902
Don't go.

898
01:14:19,503 --> 01:14:22,029
Please.

899
01:14:33,685 --> 01:14:35,845
Well?

900
01:14:35,953 --> 01:14:38,354
Computers are my forte.

901
01:14:38,457 --> 01:14:40,356
Let me see.

902
01:14:40,458 --> 01:14:44,555
"Jillian Layton. Coloring: White. Hair:
Blonde. Eyes: Blue. Height: 5 foot 4.

903
01:14:44,662 --> 01:14:47,324
Distinguishing marks:
Scar on left"...

904
01:14:47,431 --> 01:14:49,332
Is this all you've got?

905
01:14:49,434 --> 01:14:53,336
Best to take things slowly where
some women are concerned.

906
01:14:53,438 --> 01:14:55,405
Let me see.

907
01:14:55,506 --> 01:14:58,442
Hey! That's mine!

908
01:14:59,478 --> 01:15:01,377
"Layton.

909
01:15:01,479 --> 01:15:02,680
"Truck driver.

910
01:15:02,681 --> 01:15:07,278
All inquiries, reference
office of 412/L, room 5001."

911
01:15:11,622 --> 01:15:13,681
Ah, Lowry, glad I caught you.
No! Send that back!

912
01:15:13,792 --> 01:15:15,224
-Mr. Warrenn!
-Are you settling down?

913
01:15:15,248 --> 01:15:16,341
I want this order rescinded.

914
01:15:16,427 --> 01:15:19,328
There's a query about a personnel
transporter you took out from the pool.

915
01:15:19,329 --> 01:15:20,930
Tell them no. Tell them yes.

916
01:15:20,931 --> 01:15:23,492
Or was it a personnel carrier you
took out from Transportation?

917
01:15:23,601 --> 01:15:26,502
Send that up to Security.
Anyway, tidy it up, Lowry.

918
01:15:26,604 --> 01:15:28,505
There's a good chap.
And get a new suit.

919
01:15:28,606 --> 01:15:30,506
Don't you want the lift?

920
01:16:47,819 --> 01:16:51,152
Can I help you?

921
01:16:51,256 --> 01:16:54,747
<i>No! No! No! Please!</i>

922
01:16:54,859 --> 01:16:58,694
I'm, uh... I'm looking
for Officer 412/L.

923
01:16:58,796 --> 01:17:01,265
He won't be very long now.

924
01:17:02,300 --> 01:17:05,827
I thought so.

925
01:17:12,777 --> 01:17:15,404
You may go in now.

926
01:17:17,948 --> 01:17:21,042
Oh, uh, not that one.

927
01:17:21,152 --> 01:17:24,019
<i>That one. Yes.</i>

928
01:17:31,796 --> 01:17:34,730
Excuse me. Are you
Officer 412/L?

929
01:17:41,139 --> 01:17:43,106
Excuse me!

930
01:17:44,442 --> 01:17:46,136
Jack.

931
01:17:46,243 --> 01:17:48,234
Sam.

932
01:17:48,345 --> 01:17:51,109
Ah! I heard you
were coming aboard.

933
01:17:51,216 --> 01:17:55,243
Congratulations, "DZ/015."

934
01:17:55,353 --> 01:17:57,377
Thanks. Are you Officer 412/L?

935
01:17:57,488 --> 01:17:59,889
Uh-huh. That's me.

936
01:17:59,990 --> 01:18:03,289
Oh, and, Sam, a very
happy Christmas.

937
01:18:03,395 --> 01:18:05,295
-Thanks, Jack.
-Are you settling in all right?

938
01:18:05,396 --> 01:18:08,729
Yes, fine. Jack, I... I
need some information.

939
01:18:08,832 --> 01:18:11,893
Oh, Sam, this is Information
Retrieval, not Information Dispersal.

940
01:18:12,002 --> 01:18:13,903
Hey! Amy!

941
01:18:14,005 --> 01:18:15,904
Don't throw the ball
around in here.

942
01:18:16,006 --> 01:18:17,907
I'm not Amy. I'm Holly.

943
01:18:18,009 --> 01:18:20,033
Did I call you Amy, darling?
I'm sorry.

944
01:18:20,145 --> 01:18:22,078
-A triplet?
-One of them, I think.

945
01:18:22,180 --> 01:18:25,046
Barbara's taken the other
two Christmas shopping.

946
01:18:25,149 --> 01:18:28,051
You're not going to keep
calling her Barbara, are you?

947
01:18:28,153 --> 01:18:30,849
Why ever not? Barbara's a
perfectly good name, isn't it?

948
01:18:30,956 --> 01:18:33,480
Don't you like it?

949
01:18:33,591 --> 01:18:35,684
Yes, it's... fine.

950
01:18:35,793 --> 01:18:38,762
Come on. Let's get
these together.

951
01:18:38,863 --> 01:18:41,559
<i>-Jack.
-Now bring me the blue one over there.</i>

952
01:18:41,666 --> 01:18:43,565
I need to find out
about a woman.

953
01:18:43,667 --> 01:18:47,694
Come on, Chloe, let's show Uncle Sam here
how we can make the word "cat." Shall we?

954
01:18:47,805 --> 01:18:50,365
-I'm Holly.
-Sorry, love. So you are.

955
01:18:50,475 --> 01:18:52,443
-Cat.
-This is her.

956
01:18:53,712 --> 01:18:55,612
Layton.

957
01:18:55,713 --> 01:18:57,681
Oh, shit.

958
01:18:59,216 --> 01:19:01,377
-How much do you know about this?
-Uh, not much.

959
01:19:01,485 --> 01:19:03,920
What does B58/732 mean to you?

960
01:19:04,021 --> 01:19:06,922
-Buttle.
-I knew it.

961
01:19:07,024 --> 01:19:10,188
You always were
bloody quick, Sam.

962
01:19:10,295 --> 01:19:13,662
Who else knows? Warrenn?
Helpmann?

963
01:19:13,765 --> 01:19:15,994
I don't know. I only know
you got the wrong man.

964
01:19:16,100 --> 01:19:19,002
Information Transit
got the wrong man.

965
01:19:19,104 --> 01:19:21,003
I got the right man.

966
01:19:21,105 --> 01:19:22,805
The wrong man was delivered
to me as the right man.

967
01:19:22,807 --> 01:19:26,708
I accepted him on good faith
as the right man. Was I wrong?

968
01:19:27,112 --> 01:19:29,011
You killed Buttle?

969
01:19:30,114 --> 01:19:34,676
Sam, there are very rigid parameters laid
down to prevent such things happening.

970
01:19:34,786 --> 01:19:38,153
It wasn't my fault that Buttle's heart
condition didn't appear on Tuttle's file.

971
01:19:38,256 --> 01:19:40,155
Come and look. How
you getting on?

972
01:19:40,257 --> 01:19:43,226
<i>-Jack.
-A, B, C...</i>

973
01:19:43,328 --> 01:19:45,557
-I really need to know about...
-Tuttle?

974
01:19:45,662 --> 01:19:48,324
Well, we're gonna have to bring
Mr. Tuttle in, aren't we?

975
01:19:48,432 --> 01:19:51,333
And interrogate him at the
same voltage as Mr. Buttle.

976
01:19:51,435 --> 01:19:53,336
And juggle the books
in Electrical Banking.

977
01:19:53,438 --> 01:19:54,685
What has Tuttle done?

