02:07:10,037 --> 02:07:12,471
-Jack.
-How could you do this to me?

1465
02:07:12,573 --> 02:07:14,474
Jack, I'm frightened.

1466
02:07:14,576 --> 02:07:16,805
How do you think I
feel, you shit?

1467
02:07:16,912 --> 02:07:18,880
-Jack...
-Shut up!

1468
02:07:23,385 --> 02:07:27,719
This is a professional
relationship.

1469
02:07:28,823 --> 02:07:30,724
Jack.

1470
02:07:30,826 --> 02:07:34,023
Jack, no, you can't.

1471
02:07:34,128 --> 02:07:36,689
No, Jack, please.

1472
02:07:36,797 --> 02:07:38,890
<i>Jack, no! Don't!</i>

1473
02:07:39,001 --> 02:07:41,469
<i>Please, Jack! No!</i>

1474
02:08:26,547 --> 02:08:29,539
-You okay?
-Tuttle!

1475
02:08:29,650 --> 02:08:31,618
Call me Harry.

1476
02:09:19,234 --> 02:09:21,532
Let's go!

1477
02:09:52,100 --> 02:09:53,533
Here. Here.

1478
02:14:30,779 --> 02:14:34,613
Ah, Mr. Lowry. So pleased
you could make it.

1479
02:14:34,716 --> 02:14:36,979
Right this way.

1480
02:14:41,488 --> 02:14:43,457
It's a sad loss.

1481
02:14:43,557 --> 02:14:46,253
<i>Your mother was with
her at the end.</i>

1482
02:14:46,360 --> 02:14:50,592
<i>The gift of eternal life.</i>

1483
02:14:50,698 --> 02:14:55,829
Mrs. Terrain has just received
that most wonderful of gifts.

1484
02:14:55,936 --> 02:14:58,234
<i>She came to us physically new.</i>

1485
02:14:58,340 --> 02:15:02,400
<i>She goes hence from us
not so physically new.</i>

1486
02:15:02,510 --> 02:15:04,409
But the spirit never grows old.

1487
02:15:04,511 --> 02:15:07,605
Madame Lowry.

1488
02:15:11,953 --> 02:15:13,921
Mother.

1489
02:15:15,222 --> 02:15:17,122
Oh. Sam.

1490
02:15:17,225 --> 02:15:19,693
Mother. Mother!

1491
02:15:21,863 --> 02:15:24,092
Stop calling me that.

1492
02:15:25,132 --> 02:15:28,533
Mother! Mother, please!

1493
02:15:28,636 --> 02:15:32,002
-Is this guy bothering you?
-Oh. Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

1494
02:15:32,106 --> 02:15:34,939
Mother!

1495
02:15:35,042 --> 02:15:39,104
Go away. This is a
very sacred moment.

1496
02:18:48,636 --> 02:18:50,797
He's got away from us, Jack.

1497
02:18:50,905 --> 02:18:53,202
Afraid you're
right, Mr. Helpmann.

1498
02:18:53,308 --> 02:18:55,868
He's gone.

1499
02:18:58,513 --> 02:19:00,480
Well...

1500
02:19:32,245 --> 02:19:35,112
<i># Then #</i>

1501
02:19:35,216 --> 02:19:40,585
<i># Tomorrow was another day #</i>

1502
02:19:40,688 --> 02:19:44,987
<i># The morning found
me miles away #</i>

1503
02:19:46,027 --> 02:19:51,328
<i># With still
a million things to say #</i>

1504
02:19:53,768 --> 02:19:56,635
<i># Now #</i>

1505
02:19:56,737 --> 02:20:00,834
<i># As twilight gleams
the sky above #</i>

1506
02:20:02,042 --> 02:20:06,308
<i># Recalling thrills
of our love #</i>

1507
02:20:07,648 --> 02:20:12,018
<i># There's one thing
I'm certain of #</i>

1508
02:20:12,120 --> 02:20:15,021
<i># Return #</i>

1509
02:20:15,122 --> 02:20:17,921
<i># I will #</i>

1510
02:20:18,025 --> 02:20:21,484
<i># To old #</i>

1511
02:20:21,595 --> 02:20:26,123
<i># Brazil #</i>
